The paper discusses the use of deep learning for wireless communication network optimization, which falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) since the paper focuses on deep learning based on artificial neural networks. The second likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory) since the paper discusses wireless communication networks. The third likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) since the paper discusses the use of deep learning for tasks such as image classification and speech recognition. The fourth likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control) since the paper discusses the optimization of wireless communication networks. The fifth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) since the paper discusses the use of deep learning as an enabler for artificial intelligence.
